JOHANNESBURG Murder accused, Sandile Mantsoe is due to appear in the Johannesburg Magistrate Court today.The man accused of killing his ex-girlfriend Karabo Mokoena is making another bail attempt.READ: Mantsoe confessed to murdering Mokoena to sever blood-tie: NPA Mantsoe is facing charges of defeating the ends of justice. He denied killing Mokoena, suggesting she may have committed suicide.The state says Mantsoe confessed to a police officer. It's believed this was a ritual killing as Mantsoe sought to restore his business.Mokoena's charred remains were found in a shallow grave in Lyndhurst.Mantsoe was denied bail last month.eNCA